South Africa has taken a decision to make a R500 million ($33 million) payment to the Covid-19 vaccine distribution scheme co-led by the World Health Organisation, the finance ministry said on Tuesday. “We have been invited to participate in the consortium that is looking for this vaccine. … A decision has been made that South Africa is paying R500 million to participate in the process of the production of the vaccine,” Finance Minister Tito Mboweni told an economic conference on Africa. Black Friday SpecialGet 15% discount on our annual subscription!
